# CEO (Build) Review: EdTech School Connect Web Portal
slug: edtech-school-connect-web-portal
date: 2026-06-15
reviewer: ceo
verdict: pass

---

## What I actually did

I did not take the builder's self-test on faith. I spun the Flask blueprint up in
an isolated test app on port 5099 and exercised every endpoint with live curl
calls, then statically verified the frontend wiring and JS integrity.

### Backend (live-tested, not assumed)
Ran `edtech_blueprint.py` against a real `data/mw.db`. Results:

- **Auth:** parent and teacher logins both return a valid JWT with the correct
  role/name. Bad password -> `401 Invalid credentials`. No-auth request to a
  protected route -> `401 Unauthorized`. All correct.
- **Reads:** `/student`, `/grades`, `/activities`, `/messages` all return seeded
  data correctly for the parent token.
- **Role enforcement (the important part):**
  - Teacher PATCH `/grades/1` (99 / A+) -> `200`, persisted with new `updated_at`.
  - Parent PATCH `/grades/1` -> `403 Forbidden`. Correct.
  - Teacher POST `/activities` -> `201`. Parent POST `/activities` -> `403`. Correct.
- **Messaging:** parent POST `/messages` -> `201`; teacher `/messages/unread-count`
  then read 2; `/messages/read-all` -> `200`; unread-count dropped to 0. The full
  read/unread polling loop works.

All 11 endpoints behave as documented. Storage persists across requests.

### Frontend (static + integrity checks)
- `index.html` (1548 lines) inline script parses cleanly via `new Function` (no JS
  syntax errors).
- A single `apiFetch()` wrapper points at `https://api.michaelwegter.com/api/edtech`
  and every call site (`/login`, `/student`, `/grades`, `/grades/<id>`,
  `/activities`, `/messages`, `/messages/read-all`, `/messages/unread-count`)
  maps 1:1 to a real blueprint route with the right HTTP method. No orphan calls.
- CDN deps present: Chart.js 4.4.0 (jsDelivr) and Nunito/Inter (Google Fonts).
- 0 em/en dashes in `index.html` and 0 in the blueprint.

### Plumbing
- Blueprint registered in `server.py` (lines 279-280).
- `workSamples.js` entry id:7 is complete: slug, title, description, category,
  status, href (`BASE_URL + demos/<slug>/`), color, icon, frameStyle, client,
  postingSummary, builtFor, date. Schema-correct.

## Feature richness vs target (10/10)
Two distinct authenticated roles with divergent UIs; live performance dashboard
with a Chart.js radar chart that re-renders on teacher edits; inline grade
management; categorized announcements feed with teacher posting; iMessage-style
threaded messaging with 4s unread polling and badges; mobile-responsive bottom
tab bar; toasts; XSS escaping. This is a genuinely full-featured app, not a
mockup. Meets the 10/10 bar. Every mandatory/nice-to-have skill from the posting
(PHP-mappable backend, web dev, JS, HTML5) is represented, with an explicit
Flask->Laravel mapping table prepared for the proposal.

## Problems / notes
- None blocking. One nit for downstream: a seed activity string uses a
  double-hyphen ("gymnasium -- all parents welcome"). It is NOT an em/en dash so
  it passes the writing gate, but it visually reads like a dash. Optional cleanup
  for proposal-writer if it surfaces in copy; not worth a builder loop.
- The demo targets the production API, so the messaging/grades flows will only be
  exercisable in a browser once `deploy` pushes mw-backend live. That is the
  intended deployment model; `deploy` -> `deploy-test` will confirm live behavior
  next. The backend logic itself is already proven working here.

VERDICT: pass
